<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Lesson 1.1: The Hacker's Code</title>
    <style>
        :root {
            --bg: #0d1117;
            --surface: #161b22;
            --primary: #238636; /* GitHub Green */
            --terminal-green: #39ff14;
            --text: #c9d1d9;
            --danger: #f85149;
        }

        body {
            background-color: var(--bg);
            color: var(--text);
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        .wrapper {
            max-width: 800px;
            width: 100%;
        }

        /* Header Area */
        header {
            border-bottom: 2px solid var(--primary);
            padding-bottom: 10px;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }

        h1 { color: white; margin: 0; font-size: 1.8rem; }
        .status { font-family: monospace; color: var(--terminal-green); font-size: 0.9rem; }

        /* Terminal Style Section */
        .terminal {
            background: #000;
            border-radius: 6px;
            padding: 20px;
            font-family: 'Courier New', Courier, monospace;
            box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
            margin-bottom: 30px;
            border: 1px solid #30363d;
        }

        .cursor {
            display: inline-block;
            width: 10px;
            height: 18px;
            background: var(--terminal-green);
            animation: blink 1s infinite;
            vertical-align: middle;
        }

        @keyframes blink { 0%, 50% { opacity: 1; } 51%, 100% { opacity: 0; } }

        /* Cards */
        .grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; }
        .card {
            background: var(--surface);
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            border: 1px solid #30363d;
        }
        .card h3 { margin-top: 0; color: var(--terminal-green); }
        .card.black { border-top: 4px solid var(--danger); }
        .card.white { border-top: 4px solid var(--primary); }

        /* Button & Interaction */
        .btn {
            background: var(--primary);
            color: white;
            border: none;
            padding: 12px 24px;
            border-radius: 6px;
            cursor: pointer;
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-top: 20px;
            transition: 0.3s;
        }
        .btn:hover { opacity: 0.8; }

        .hidden { display: none; }
        
        input {
            background: transparent;
            border: none;
            color: var(--terminal-green);
            font-family: inherit;
            font-size: inherit;
            outline: none;
            width: 80%;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="wrapper">
    <header>
        <div class="status">> SESSION_ESTABLISHED: 127.0.0.1</div>
        <h1>1.1 The Ethical Hacker's Code</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="terminal" id="terminal-box">
        <p style="color: var(--terminal-green)">[SYSTEM] To access the Rules of Engagement, type "decrypt" and press Enter:</p>
        <p>> <input type="text" id="cmdInput" autofocus></p>
    </div>

    <div id="mainContent" class="hidden">
        <section>
            <h2>Mission Parameters</h2>
            <p>Knowledge is a weapon. In this course, we don't just teach you how to use the tools; we teach you how to remain a professional. To succeed, you must distinguish yourself from the chaos.</p>
            
            <div class="grid">
                <div class="card white">
                    <h3>White Hat</h3>
                    <p>Authorized. Legal. Helpful. You hack to find vulnerabilities so they can be patched before the bad guys find them.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="card black">
                    <h3>Black Hat</h3>
                    <p>Unauthorized. Malicious. Selfish. These individuals destroy value and steal data for personal gain.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section style="margin-top: 40px;">
            <h3>The 3 Golden Laws</h3>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Written Permission:</strong> Never touch a box without a signed contract.</li>
                <li><strong>Scope:</strong> If the client says "Test the Web App," do NOT test their Wi-Fi.</li>
                <li><strong>Data Integrity:</strong> Look, but don't touch. If you find sensitive data, report it and stop.</li>
            </ol>
            <button class="btn" onclick="alert('Proceed to Skool and comment I AGREE to unlock Module 1.2!')">I Understand the Code</button>
        </section>
    </div>
</div>

<script>
    const input = document.getElementById('cmdInput');
    const terminal = document.getElementById('terminal-box');
    const content = document.getElementById('mainContent');

    input.addEventListener('keypress', function (e) {
        if (e.key === 'Enter') {
            const val = input.value.toLowerCase();
            if (val === 'decrypt') {
                terminal.innerHTML = '<p style="color: var(--terminal-green)">[SUCCESS] Access Granted. Decrypting file...</p>';
                setTimeout(() => {
                    terminal.classList.add('hidden');
                    content.classList.remove('hidden');
                }, 1000);
            } else {
                alert('Access Denied. Try typing "decrypt"');
                input.value = '';
            }
        }
    });
</script>

</body>
</html>
